===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Two different theories:
* {{liushu|p}} of a fetus (it can be seen in {{zh-l|*包}}, {{zh-l|*胞}}. In 包, the radical should represent the placenta. 胞 today means "cell").
* {{liushu|p}} of a snake (therefore, it should be similar to {{zh-l|*巴}}). This theory is found in the Shuowen Jiezi, which however is not based on oracle bones versions of characters.
The character is similar to {{zh-l|*已}}, which cannot be found in the Shuowen Jiezi.

===Etymology 1===
{{och-l|巳|tr=s-ləʔ}} displaced {{och-l|子|tr=tsəʔ}}, the original sixth earthly branch which denoted the moon's "coming forth" stage (i.e. early waning-gibbous phase) "due to phonological closeness (combined with the semantic opacity of the Branch terms at later eras)" ({{zh-ref|Smith, 2011}}).

Association with the snake was possibly arbitrary, analogous to how [[辰]], the fifth earthly branch, was arbitrarily associated with the dragon ({{zh-ref|Ferlus, 2013}}).

