{{wp|ja:}}
Assumed to be an abbreviation of {{ja-r|蛇|へみ|[[snake]]|pos=modern reading ''hebi''}}.<ref name="KDJ2Omis"/><ref name="K">{{R:Kojien}}</ref>

Philological analyses presume this was read as ''mi{{sub|2}}'' in Old Japanese, as names {{m|ojp|2=|3=身麻呂|tr=mi{{sub|2}}maro{{sub|2}}|t=a male born on the year of the Snake}} and {{m|ojp|2=|3=身売|tr=mi{{sub|2}}me{{sub|1}}|t=a female born on the year of the Snake}} were recorded in {{w|Shōsōin|Shōsōin documents}}, alongside other names born on the {{w|Chinese zodiac}}.<ref name="JDBmi">{{R:JDB|pages=696-697}}</ref><ref name="KDJ2Omis"/>

